Fragrance Classification Project¶

The purpose of the project is to accurately classify the fragrances 1, 2, 3 & 4 based on the data logged on 12 different human subjects on the brainwave activities in the alpha, delta and theta wave spectrum. 20 channels of 5 explanatory variables - alpha wave, delta wave, theta wave, sample entropy and Higuchi Fractal Dimension - are given for every row. The approach for the project shown in the notebook is to visualise the data, clean the data and, finally, model the data to determine highest accuracy score.

Data is visualised using matplotlib to identify their distribution and determine the best data cleaning techniques.

To clean the data, columns found to have logarithmic distributions are logged (using natural logarithm) and scaled using MinMaxScaler from Scikit-Learn. Dimension reduction techniques are also applied to engineer variables that contains information from all the columns.

Lastly, five machine learning modelling techniques are used after each data cleaning method:

  • Logistic Regression,
  • K-Nearest Neighbour Classifier,
  • Support Vector Machine,
  • Random Forest Classifier and,
  • Decision Tree Classifier

to classify the fragrances. An accuracy score is then calculated based on whether the model predicted the test dataset correctly and a confusion matrix is shown to see the accuracy across the 4 fragrances. An average accuracy score is calculated too using StratifiedKFold cross validation technique that randomly splits training and test data to 5-fold splits.

Conclusion: Removing the rows that contain outliers beyond 3 standard deviations, reduce the dimensions using linear discriminant analysis and modelling with logistic regression produced the highest average accuracy score of 89.5%.

Data Visualisation¶

Delta brainwaves for some subject-patient pairing¶

In [4]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def getColumns(waveType):
    columnList = []
    for channel_number in range(1, 21):
        columnList.append('ch{}{}'.format(channel_number, waveType))
    return columnList
In [5]:
waveType = 'Delta'

for idx in range(0, df.shape[0], 40):
    df01 = df[df.index == idx]
    subject = df01.iloc[0]['subject']
    fragrance = df01.iloc[0]['fragance']
    
    print('Data for Subject {}, Fragrance {}'.format(subject, fragrance))

    columns = getColumns(waveType)
    df02 = df01[columns]
    vals = df02.values.tolist()[0][0:]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(15,5))
    plt.title('Values of {}'.format(waveType))
    plt.xlabel('Channel Number')
    plt.ylabel('{} values'.format(waveType))
    plt.scatter(np.arange(1,21), vals)
    plt.show()

Using Decision Tree Classifier¶

In [17]:
ccp_alpha_list = [0, 0.0001,0.001,0.01,0.1]
criterion_list = ['gini', 'entropy']

highest_accuracy = 0
highest_ccp_alpha = 0
highest_criterion = ''

for ccp_alpha_val in ccp_alpha_list:
  for criterion_val in criterion_list:
      dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion=criterion_val, ccp_alpha=ccp_alpha_val)
      dt.fit(X_train, y_train)
      y_pred = dt.predict(X_test)
      accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
      if accuracy > highest_accuracy:
        highest_accuracy = accuracy
        highest_ccp_alpha = ccp_alpha_val
        highest_criterion = criterion_val
print(highest_ccp_alpha, highest_criterion)

dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion=highest_criterion, ccp_alpha=highest_ccp_alpha)
dt.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred = dt.predict(X_test)
print('Accuracy score:', accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
print(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))

Modelling (after dealing with outliers)¶

Try Numpy.log brainwaves with MinMaxScaler and LDA¶

Conclusion: Highest accuracy score is 71.7% using support vector machine.

In [24]:
def getColumnsWithoutFragrance(waveType):
  columns = []
  for i in range(1, 21):
    columns.append('ch{}{}'.format(i, waveType))
  return columns

output=[]

def removeNestings(l):
    for i in l: 
        if type(i) == list: 
            removeNestings(i) 
        else: 
            output.append(i)

cols_wave = []
cols_wave.append(getColumnsWithoutFragrance('Delta'))
cols_wave.append(getColumnsWithoutFragrance('Theta'))
cols_wave.append(getColumnsWithoutFragrance('Alpha'))
removeNestings(cols_wave)
cols_wave = output
print(len(cols_wave))

df03 = df.copy()

df03[cols_wave] = np.log(df03[cols_wave])
columns = df.columns[2:]

X = df03[columns]
y = df03[['fragance']]

scaler = MinMaxScaler()
X = pd.DataFrame(scaler.fit_transform(X))

lda = LinearDiscriminantAnalysis()
X_lda = lda.fit_transform(X, y.values.ravel())
print(lda.explained_variance_ratio_)

for train_index, test_index in skf.split(X, y):
  X_train, y_train = train_test_split(train_index, random_state=42, test_size=0.2)
  X_train = X_lda.iloc[train_index]
  y_train = y.iloc[train_index]

  logreg_score.append(accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
  
  knn = KNeighborsClassifier()
  knn.fit(X_train, y_train.values.ravel())
  y_pred = knn.predict(X_test)
  print('KNN Accuracy Score:', accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
  knn_score.append(accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))

  svc = SVC()
  svc.fit(X_train, y_train.values.ravel())
  y_pred = svc.predict(X_test)
  print('Support Vector Accuracy Score:', accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
  svc_score.append(accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))

  clf = RandomForestClassifier()
  clf.fit(X_train, y_train.values.ravel())
  y_pred = clf.predict(X_test)
  print('Random Forest Accuracy Score:', accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
  clf_score.append(accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))

  dt = DecisionTreeClassifier()
  dt.fit(X_train, y_train)
  y_pred = dt.predict(X_test)
  print('Decision Tree Classifier Accuracy Score:', accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
  dt_score.append(accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))

print('\n')

from scipy import stats
from numpy import median

columns = df.columns[2:]

def getColumnsWithoutFragrance(waveType):
  columns = []
  for i in range(1, 21):
    columns.append('ch{}{}'.format(i, waveType))
  return columns

output=[]

def removeNestings(l):
    for i in l: 
        if type(i) == list: 
            removeNestings(i) 
        else: 
            output.append(i)

cols_wave = []
cols_wave.append(getColumnsWithoutFragrance('Delta'))
cols_wave.append(getColumnsWithoutFragrance('Theta'))
cols_wave.append(getColumnsWithoutFragrance('Alpha'))
removeNestings(cols_wave)
cols_wave = output

df03 = df.copy()
df03[cols_wave] = np.log10(df03[cols_wave])
df03[columns] = pd.DataFrame(stats.zscore(df03[columns]))
for i in columns:
  median = df03.loc[df03[i] > -3, i].median()
  df03.loc[df03[i] > 3, i] = np.nan
  df03.loc[df03[i] < -3, i] = np.nan
  df03.fillna(median,inplace=True)
df03
